cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with image reconstruction from JPEG compressed format, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). The paper also discusses the use of signal priors, which is a common topic in machine learning (MM) and information theory (IT). The paper also introduces a new graph-signal smoothness prior, which is related to graph theory (GR) and can be seen as a form of regularization in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.GR.
